<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870715-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Cubic Gets Navy JobTotaling $74.4 Million</HL><DD> 07/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CUB TXT KAMNA CDADEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Cubic Corp. was awarded a $74.4 million Navy contract for installing air crew combat-training systems at various bases.    Avco Corp., a unit of Textron Inc., received a $33 million Air Force contract for re-entry vehicle components.    CBI Na-Con Inc. got a $28.8 million Navy contract for ship-model test facilities.    Kaman Aerospace Corp. was issued a $14.7 million addition to an Air Force contract for Strategic Defense Initiative electronics.    Control Data Corp. won an $11.7 million Army contract for classified electronics. </TEXT></DOC>